## Prioritized Remediation Plan

| Priority | Smell | Fix | Why first |
|----------|-------|-----|-----------|
| 1 | Assertion-Free Test | Add assertions | Prevents false-pass — highest risk to confidence |
| 2 | Conditional Test Logic | Split into 2 tests | Hidden untested path — coverage lie |
| 3 | Sleepy Test | Use async/await or signaling | Flaky failures + slows suite |
| 4 | Mystery Guest | Inline CSV data | Broken on every machine but the author's |
| 5 | Exception Handling | Use `Assert.ThrowsException` | Quick swap, eliminates silent-catch risk |
| 6 | Sensitive Equality | Assert on properties | Quick swap, removes formatting fragility |
| 7 | Magic Numbers | Use computed constants | Improves readability, moderate effort |
| 8 | Eager Test | Test through orchestrator | Requires understanding the workflow API |
| 9 | General Fixture | Delete unused `_logger` | One-line fix, lowest impact |

**Bottom line:** 8 of 9 tests have at least one smell. The highest-risk issues are the assertion-free test (false confidence) and the conditional logic (untested branch). Those two should be fixed first.
